com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.mem
Interface DynamicLibrary

All Known Subinterfaces:
JNIEasyLibrary
public interface DynamicLibrary

The DynamicLibrary interface represents a loaded Dynamic Link Library (DLL) by the framework.

Using this interface, DLL's exported native methods and fields are accessible to the Java world using internal framework classes and public using specific interfaces.

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria
See Also:
DLLManager

addDLLBehavior

DLLBehavior addDLLBehavior(java.lang.String nativeName,
                           java.lang.Class proxyInterf,
                           NativeBehaviorSignature sig)
Returns a native proxy of the DLL's exported C or C++ method or field with the specified name.

If not exist a method with this nativeName and signature sig, a new proxy native instance implementing the specified interface proxyInterf is created, registered and returned, else found native instance is returned.

It is possible to register several native proxy instances of the same DLL method (same native name), because a native method can be called using several "formal" signatures (for instance: a const char* formal parameter can receive an int parameter).

The specified proxy interface proxyInterf must be compatible with the specified signature sig (if CPPConstructor, signature must be NativeConstructorSignature and so on).

Valid interfaces: CPPConstructor, CMethod, CPPMethod, CFieldMethod

The specified name can be a native name expression as explained in NativeTypeManager.parseNameWithMacros(String), this method is internally called to get the native name.

Parameters:
nativeName - the exported name of the method in the DLL.
proxyInterf - interface used as proxy
sig - the native signature of the exported method or field.
Returns:
a native proxy instance of the DLL method.
See Also:
findBehaviorByName(String,NativeBehaviorSignature), NativeTypeManager.decBehavior(Class,NativeBehaviorSignature)

addDLLBehavior

DLLBehavior addDLLBehavior(java.lang.String nativeName,
                           NativeBehaviorSignature sig)
Returns a native proxy of the DLL's exported C or C++ method or field with the specified name.

The appropriate native proxy interface is selected according the specified signature.

Current implementation is: 

        Class nativeInterf;
        if (sig instanceof NativeConstructorSignature)
            nativeInterf = CPPConstructor.class;        
        else if (sig instanceof NativeMethodSignature)
        {
            if (sig instanceof NativeStaticMethodSignature)
                nativeInterf = CMethod.class;
            else // (sig instanceof NativeInstanceMethodSignature)
                nativeInterf = CPPMethod.class;            
        }
        else // (sig instanceof FieldMethodSignature)
        {
            if (sig instanceof NativeStaticFieldMethodSignature)
                nativeInterf = CFieldMethod.class;
            else
                throw new JNIEasyException("Invalid signature, not exist C++ exported fields");
        }            
        return addDLLBehavior(nativeName,nativeInterf,sig);

Parameters:
nativeName - the exported name of the method in the DLL.
sig - the native signature of the exported method or field.
Returns:
a native proxy instance of the DLL method.
See Also:
addDLLBehavior(String,Class,NativeBehaviorSignature)

findBehaviorsByName

java.util.Collection findBehaviorsByName(java.lang.String nativeName)
Returns an unmodifiable Collection with the registered native method instances with the specified native name.

If this DLL is the JNIEasyLibrary, this collection may contain Java callbacks (exported with JNIEasyLibrary.exportBehavior(String,NativeBehavior), this instances does not implement the DLLBehavior interface. Use the NativeBehavior interface to a secure iteration of elements.

Returns:
a name indexed unmodifiable Map of native method instances.
